wren
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:<i>Xenicus</i> sp. (occas. popularly and mistakenly <i>Acanthisitta chloris</i> rifleman; and <i>Gerygone igata</i> grey warbler, see 1923 cit.); a tiny bird with an erect tail, also called matuhituhi, riroriro
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:also bush wren
Pronunciation:
Notes: (Cf riroriro 1859)
Citations
